  <mads:note displayLabel="Smith's Dictionary">"Metrophanes, Of Eucarpia, in Phrygia (comp. Steph. Byz. s. v. Εὐκαρπια), 
      wrote a work on Phrygia, and also the following treatises on rhetoric: -- ερὶ ἰδεῶν λόγου, Περὶ στάσεων, and commentaries
      on Hermogenes and Aristides, in consequence of which he is regarded by some as the author of the Scholia on Aristides.
      (Westermann, Gescl. der Griech. Beredtsamkeit, § 104, n. 15.)....."</mads:note>
